com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface SeriesEntry


  • public interface SeriesEntry
    An entry in a Series container that can house other container types only. Series is a uniform type, where Series.containerType indicates the single type housed in each entry. As entries are received, they are appended to any previously received entries.
    See Also:
    Series

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clears SeriesEntry object. Useful for object reuse during encoding. While decoding, SeriesEntry object can be reused without using clear().

      • encode

        int encode(EncodeIterator iter)
        Encodes single series item, "moving" to the next row if necessary. Must be called after encodeSetDefsComplete() and/or encodeSummaryDataComplete(). Typical use:
        1. Call Series.encodeInit()
        2. Call SeriesEntry.encode() for each entry using the same buffer
        3. Call Series.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • encodeInit

        int encodeInit(EncodeIterator iter,
               int maxEncodingSize)
        Prepare a single series item for encoding. Must be called after encodeSetDefsComplete() and/or encodeSummaryDataComplete(). Typical use:
        1. Call Series.encodeInit()
        2. Call SeriesEntry.encodeInit()..SeriesEntry.encodeComplete() for each entry using the same buffer
        3. Call Series.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator
        maxEncodingSize - max encoding size of the data
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • encodeComplete

        int encodeComplete(EncodeIterator iter,
                   boolean success)
        Completes a series element encoding. Typical use:
        1. Call Series.encodeInit()
        2. Call SeriesEntry.encodeInit()..SeriesEntry.encodeComplete() for each entry using the same buffer
        3. Call Series.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        success - If true - successfully complete the aggregate, if false - remove the aggregate from the buffer.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator
